You can dynamically populate a picklist in a Visualforce page by using a list in the controller and looping through it to create picklist options. Here's an example code snippet to create a picklist dynamically in the Visualforce page and controller in Salesforce:

Visualforce Page:
```
<apex:page controller="PicklistController">
    <apex:form >
        <apex:selectList value="{!selectedValue}" size="1">
            <apex:selectOptions value="{!picklistValues}" />
        </apex:selectList>
    </apex:form>
</apex:page>
```

Controller Class:
```
public class PicklistController {
  public String selectedValue { get; set; }
  public List<SelectOption> picklistValues { get; set; }

  public PicklistController() {
    picklistValues = new List<SelectOption>();
    picklistValues.add(new SelectOption('--None--', '--None--'));
    picklistValues.add(new SelectOption('Option 1', 'Option 1'));
    picklistValues.add(new SelectOption('Option 2', 'Option 2'));
    picklistValues.add(new SelectOption('Option 3', 'Option 3'));
  }
}
```

In this code, we're defining a `List<SelectOption>` in the controller called `picklistValues` which will be used to dynamically populate the picklist options. We've also defined `selectedValue` to bind the selected value to a controller variable.

In the constructor of the controller class, we're adding options to the picklistValues list. In this example, we've added four options to the list: "--None--", "Option 1", "Option 2", and "Option 3". You can modify this list based on your requirements.

In the Visualforce page, we are using the `apex:selectList` and `apex:selectOptions` tags to create the picklist. The `value` attribute of `apex:selectList` binds the selected value to the controller variable `selectedValue`. The picklist options are created using the `apex:selectOptions` tag, which binds to the `picklistValues` list in the controller.

Using this code, you can dynamically populate the picklist options in your Visualforce page by updating the `picklistValues` list in the controller class.
